.SH "NAME"
Reply::Plugin::Colors \- colorize output
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.42
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\&  ; .replyrc
\&  [Colors]
\&  error   = bright red
\&  warning = bright yellow
\&  result  = bright green
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This plugin adds coloring to the results when they are printed to the screen.
By default, errors are \f(CW\*(C`red\*(C'\fR, warnings are \f(CW\*(C`yellow\*(C'\fR, and normal results are
\&\f(CW\*(C`green\*(C'\fR, although this can be overridden through configuration as shown in the
synopsis. Term::ANSIColor is used to generate the colors, so any value that
is accepted by that module is a valid value for the \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`warning\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`result\*(C'\fR options.
